# m6_p09_tile_oneway_collide.shot — M6 P09
#
# Regression for the TILE_F_ONE_WAY collision wire-up at
# src/physics.c::collide_map_one_pass + the kinematic ray-cast in
# src/level.c::level_ray_hits_kinematic.
#
# Scenario: Concourse map (clean overhead, mid-screen empty rows).
# Paint a 10-tile-wide ONE_WAY strip at row 35 (y=1120..1152). Spawn
# mech high above the strip. Three captures:
#   t=80  — mech has fallen and LANDED on top of the strip (proves
#           "from above" still blocks).
#   t=140 — mech is JET-ing up through the strip (proves "from below"
#           is passable).
#   t=200 — mech rests above the strip again (proves the constraint
#           solver doesn't permanently sandwich it).
#
# Pre-fix: TILE_F_ONE_WAY was honored by polys but ignored by the
# tile branch — the editor's checkbox lied. Post-fix:
#   - physics_integrate uses level_ray_hits_kinematic which lets the
#     particle pass through on upward sweeps.
#   - collide_map_one_pass adds a velocity-sign check so falling
#     contacts block but rising contacts pass.

window 1920 1080
seed   42 42
out    build/shots/m6_p09_tile_oneway_collide

# Concourse: 100×60 = 3200×1920 px. Plenty of clean air in the
# middle. The atrium is mostly open between rows 20 and 50.
map concourse

# Paint a one-tile-tall ONE_WAY strip at row 35 (y=1120..1152), tiles
# x=44..54 (centered around the map middle at column 50).
# Flags: 0x09 = TILE_F_SOLID | TILE_F_ONE_WAY.
paint_rect 44 35 55 36 0x09

# Spawn high above the strip — well above any of concourse's existing
# atrium geometry (highest mid-platform is row 22 at y=704; spawn at
# y=720 puts the mech in the open atrium just below that).
spawn_at 1600 720
mouse    1600 540

# t=80 (~1.3 s of fall): mech has landed on the strip. Pelvis should
# be at y ≈ (35*32) - 36 = 1084.
at  80 shot 1_landed

# Jet up from t=85 — start a sustained jet to escape the strip.
at  85 press jet
at 130 release jet
# t=140: jet released; mech should be well above the strip.
at 140 shot 2_jetted_up

# t=200: mech falls back; settles on top of the strip again.
at 200 shot 3_resettled
at 230 end

contact_sheet oneway_collide cols 3 cell 640 360
